text.tspan: Where an obstruction of greater than 2 in. is encountered, the buried
service guard (item am) shall be divided as shown (from the NID, BET, or
fused protector to the obstruction, and from 3 in. below the obstruction to
6 in. below the ground). In lieu of divided service guards (item am), a
continuous flexible conduit may be used from the NID, BET, or fused
protector to 6 in. below the ground.
Where an obstruction of less than 2 in. is encountered, the buried service
guard (item am) shall extend from the NID, BET, or fused protector
For converting English units to metric units use 1 in. = 25.4 mm and
